I loveeee CHIPOTLE. But being honest as healthy as it is if you eat too much of it the pounds will show. Thus, in order to still get my weekly (sometimes daily) Chipotle fix I've settled on just getting two of my favorite sides per visit opposed to getting an entire bowl. I get a side of guacamole and a side of protein (usually steak) and that's generally my meal. I have tried several Chipotles within a 2 mile radius of this one but baby let me tell you 2600 Connecticut Ave. never disappoints. I usually struggle with flavoring when it comes to Chipotle locations in general. You go in one day and the food is seasoned to perfection but then you go back to the SAME location 3 days later and its bland like hospital food. At 2600 Connecticut Ave. my steak is ALWAYS perfectly seasoned and the guacamole is always fresh with the right ingredients. No matter who is working the kitchen or the line that day its consistently the same. I have been coming to this chipotle for months now and not once have I been surprised by what the meat or sides taste like. Its always perfect. Not to mention they are always fast and to the point. I loveee this Chipotle, and whoever manages it or whoever is working magic back there in the kitchen should be commended! -Z
